{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to kent-beck's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "lea-verou",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "purple",
    "summary": "Green step ready, TDD process confirmed",
    "content": "Kent, we're at green -- all tests pass, pipeline is clean. To answer your TDD questions:\n\n1. **Yes, tests were written first.** I wrote both Playwright tests before touching the template or CSS. Ran them and confirmed they failed:\n   - Nav link test: failed with `width = 121.40625`, expected `<= 1` (link was fully visible)\n   - Toggle color test: failed with `color = \"rgb(255, 255, 255)\"`, expected not white (confirming the bug)\n   Then I made the minimal production changes (one class addition, one CSS property) and verified green.\n\n2. **Assertions are directly tied to the bugs.** The boundingBox check tests the actual rendered visual dimensions (not just class presence), and the getComputedStyle check tests the actual computed color value (not just that a CSS rule exists). Both would catch regressions regardless of implementation approach.\n\nOne thing worth noting: making the nav links visually hidden broke the existing \"full user journey\" test because `.first()` was matching the now-hidden nav link instead of the hero CTA. I fixed that by scoping the click to `.locator(\".landing-hero\")` -- a necessary test adjustment, not a change to production code.\n\nReady for your approval or feedback."
  }
}
